prvtSwitchAccessListMib.name: prvtSwitchAccessListMib

revisions.description: Addeed accessListInterfaceRateStatistics object
Added accessListSapTable and accessListSapStatisticsTable
Added new OIDs standardAccessListDropLevel, extendedAccessListDropLevel, macAccessListDropLevel, standardAccessListDscp, extendedAccessListDscp
Created AccessListRemarkString TC.
Added objects for Egress Access Lists
Added Access List Interface Statistics
Removed redefined OIDs in private vendor extension definitions.
Added the tag filter object in the interface and VLAN access group tables and changed some description with TMetro specific information.
Switched the values of greater-than and less-than in PortDef textual convention.
Changed the Rate textual convention to include the value of 0 (zero).
Added the span track objects in the interface tables.
Added the source and destination range objects in the extended access list table.
Fixed spelling errors and changed the contact info.

1. accessListControlTable is now indexed only by accessListControlListGroup and the row status creates whole groups. 2. Added standardAccessListIndex and extendedAccessListIndex as indices of standardAccessListTable and extendedAccessListTable to replace accessGroupControlListIndex. 3. Added standardAccessListRowStatus and extendedAccessListRowStatus to enable creation of rules. Rules, however, cannot be deleted using these objects. 4. Added support for enabling the loggin of ACLs (standardAccessListLog, extendedAccessListLog). 5. Added support for redirection traffic to a vlan and ip next hop (accessListInterfaceRedirectVlanID, accessListVLANRedirectVlanID, accessListInterfaceRedirectNexthop, accessListVLANRedirectNexthop). 6. Added objects for configuring the Peak rate and peak burst when dual rate limit is used. (accessListInterfacePeakRate, accessListInterfacePeakBurst, accessListVLANPeakRate, accessListVLANPeakBurst) 7. Added objects for toggling the traffic metering color awareness and remarking policy. (accessListInterfaceColorAware, accessListVlanColorAware, accessListInterfacePolicy, accessListVlanPolicy)

Global changes: 1. Added support for VLAN IP access-group. 2. Added support for redirecting traffic to an interface (accessListInterfaceRedirectIfIndex, accessListVLANRedirectIfIndex). 3. Renamed accessListControlListGroupIndex to accessListInterfaceGroupIndex 4. Changes in AccessListAction, removed shaper. 5. Removed Burst TEXTUAL-CONVENTION. Changes for E-Series 1. Introduced changes in PortDef, ExceedAction, AccessListDiscard TEXTUAL-CONVENTION for E-Series. 2. The objects extendedAccessListIgmpType and accessListInterfaceShaper are not supported for E-Series. 3. Added accessListInterfaceBurst, accessListVLANBurst for E-Series. 4. The range of accessListInterfaceDscp is now 0..63 for E-Series.
Moved to SMI-V2. Removed extendedAccessListEstablished and extendedAccessListMSS.
Changed mapping of AccessListAction enum.
Added shaper to access group.
Added ICMP type, ICMP code and IGMP to extended access list.
Added access group with rate limit.
Added routed ISP.
1. Added remark, MSS and Established to access list. 2. Added Priority and Discard to access group.
Added the ability to modify TOS in extended access list.
Added shaper mode for access list action.
Added support for access group in ISP.
Initial version.

prvtSwitchAccessListMib.description: The access-list MIB module that controls L3 switches access-list parameters

AccessListAction.name: AccessListAction
AccessListAction.description: The AccessListAction type represents action taken when this access-list condition are asserted.

IpProtocol.name: IpProtocol
IpProtocol.description: The IpProtocol type represents the protocol number in the IP datagram header

PortDef.name: PortDef
PortDef.description: The PortDef type operates together with the port number filed inside the access-list & control how the port number is being processed. The values greater-than(3) and less-than(4) are supported only on E-Series family boards

Rate.name: Rate
Rate.description: The Rate type represents in Kbps the maximum rate limit for the flow

ExceedAction.name: ExceedAction
ExceedAction.description: the ExceedAction type represents the action that the switch should take when one of the limits exceeded: drop -> drop the packets, markDiscardable this packet is discardable if a conjection ocure Only the E-Series family boards support the values green, yellow and red. Other values are not supported by the E-Series

VlanTag.name: VlanTag
VlanTag.description: The VlanTag type represents if the VLAN is tagged or untagged.

ISPType.name: ISPType
ISPType.description: The ISPType type represents the ISP type - either connective or normal.

Shaper.name: Shaper
Shaper.description: The Shaper type represents the status of the shaper

ConformAction.name: ConformAction
ConformAction.description: The action to perform if the condition is matched.

AssigenValue.name: AssigenValue
AssigenValue.description: Enables/disables assignment of an ISP user to this interface.

AccessListModifyTos.name: AccessListModifyTos
AccessListModifyTos.description: The AccessListModifyTos must be enabled if the user wants the ToS to be modified.

AccessListEstablished.name: AccessListEstablished
AccessListEstablished.description: Match established connection (ACK or RST flages)

AccessListDiscard.name: AccessListDiscard
AccessListDiscard.description: Mark discardable or normal for priority on access group Only the E-Series family and the G-Series family boards support the values green, yellow and red. Other values are not supported by the E-Series and G-series.

accessListTemplate.name: accessListTemplate
accessListTemplate.description: The access-list template in use. For non E-series devices, the device must be restarted for this setting to take effect.

accessListControlTable.name: accessListControlTable
accessListControlTable.description: This table controls the creation or removal of a access-list group from all access-list tables. The real programming of values is done in the coresponding access-list table.

accessListControlEntry.name: accessListControlEntry
accessListControlEntry.description: An entry in the accessListControlTable table.

accessListControlListGroup.name: accessListControlListGroup
accessListControlListGroup.description: This object identifies the index of the group of access-list rules Each range of group indexes is related to a different access-list type 1..99 for standard access-list 100..199 for extended access-list.

accessListControlRowStatus.name: accessListControlRowStatus
accessListControlRowStatus.description: This indicates the row status & enables creation & deletion of lines in this table. See SNMPv2-TC for more information.

standardAccessListTable.name: standardAccessListTable
standardAccessListTable.description: This table contains standard access-list parameters.

standardAccessListEntry.name: standardAccessListEntry
standardAccessListEntry.description: An entry in the standardAccessListTable table.

standardAccessListIndex.name: standardAccessListIndex
standardAccessListIndex.description: Index of the particular rule of the group.

standardAccessListAction.name: standardAccessListAction
standardAccessListAction.description: The action to preform if the condition of this access-list rule condition is true.

standardAccessListIpSrc.name: standardAccessListIpSrc
standardAccessListIpSrc.description: The IP source address associated with this flow.

standardAccessListIpMASKsrc.name: standardAccessListIpMASKsrc
standardAccessListIpMASKsrc.description: The IP mask that, together with standardAccessListIpSrc, defines the subnet.

standardAccessListLog.name: standardAccessListLog
standardAccessListLog.description: Enable normal or extended logging of this access-list rule.

standardAccessListVpt.name: standardAccessListVpt
standardAccessListVpt.description: This object is meaningful : 1.when vlan-priority template is used and will reprezent vlan priority tag. 2.Forwarding class reprezented in the second part of enumeration: fc-##. A value of 8 means that neither of above is defined.

standardAccessListRowStatus.name: standardAccessListRowStatus
standardAccessListRowStatus.description: This indicates the row status & enables creation of rows in this table. In order to be consistent with ACL policy, this object does not allow deletion of rules. The entire group must be deleted and all rules removed at once.

standardAccessListVlanId.name: standardAccessListVlanId
standardAccessListVlanId.description: This object shows the customer VLAN. The object is meaningful only if standardAccessListVlanMask is set.

standardAccessListVlanMask.name: standardAccessListVlanMask
standardAccessListVlanMask.description: This object shows the customer VLAN mask. It is meaningful only if standardAccessListVlanId is set. The value is in hexadecimal type DisplayString (0xXXX).

standardAccessListProviderVlanId.name: standardAccessListProviderVlanId
standardAccessListProviderVlanId.description: This object shows the provider VLAN. The object is meaningful only if standardAccessListProviderVlanMask is set.

standardAccessListProviderVlanMask.name: standardAccessListProviderVlanMask
standardAccessListProviderVlanMask.description: This object shows the provider VLAN mask. It is meaningful only if standardAccessListProviderVlanId is set. The value is in hexadecimal type DisplayString (0xXXX)

standardAccessListProviderVpt.name: standardAccessListProviderVpt
standardAccessListProviderVpt.description: This object shows the provider VLAN priority tag. A value of 8 means undefined.

standardAccessListUntaggedMode.name: standardAccessListUntaggedMode
standardAccessListUntaggedMode.description: This object enables the untagged mode

standardAccessListDscp.name: standardAccessListDscp
standardAccessListDscp.description: The object shows the DiffServ Point (DSCP) value from IP header.

extendedAccessListPortRangeDst.name: extendedAccessListPortRangeDst

macAccessListMacSrc.description: The object contains the MAC address of source. If this object is not set, the result is 'any' source mac address. If object macAccessListMacSrcMask is not set, this object means the host address.

macAccessListMacSrcMask.name: macAccessListMacSrcMask
macAccessListMacSrcMask.description: This object contains the mask for MAC source address. The object affects macAccessListMacSrc, defines host or range.

macAccessListMacDst.name: macAccessListMacDst
macAccessListMacDst.description: The object contains the MAC address of destination. If this object is not set, the result is 'any' destination mac address. If object macAccessListMacDstMask is not set, this object means the host address.

macAccessListMacDstMask.name: macAccessListMacDstMask

macAccessListUntaggedMode.name: macAccessListUntaggedMode

accessListInterfaceTableIndex.name: accessListInterfaceTableIndex

accessListInterfaceGroupIndex.name: accessListInterfaceGroupIndex
accessListInterfaceGroupIndex.description: This indicates the index of the access group for this interface. This value is the same as the value of accessListControlListGroup for the assigned ACL.

accessListInterfaceRowStatus.name: accessListInterfaceRowStatus
accessListInterfaceRowStatus.description: This indicates the row status & enables creation & deletion of lines in this (and related) tables. See SNMPv2-TC for more information.

accessListInterfacePriority.description: Priority level value. Valid values are 0 to 7, 8 means undefined.

accessListInterfaceRedirectIfIndex.name: accessListInterfaceRedirectIfIndex
accessListInterfaceRedirectIfIndex.description: This object controls redirection of traffic matching this ACG. If the value is a valid ifIndex, the traffic will be redirected to it. If the value is 0 redirection is disabled. Setting this object requires that accessListInterfaceRedirectVlanID is also set.

accessListInterfaceRedirectVlanID.name: accessListInterfaceRedirectVlanID
accessListInterfaceRedirectVlanID.description: This object controls redirection of traffic matching this ACG. If the value is a valid VLAN ID, the traffic will be redirected to it. If the value is 0 redirection is disabled. If the device is TMetro, this object sets the tag substitution policy for this access group

accessListInterfaceRedirectNexthop.name: accessListInterfaceRedirectNexthop
accessListInterfaceRedirectNexthop.description: This object controls redirection of traffic matching this ACG. If the value is a valid IP address then the traffic will be redirected to it. If the value is 0 redirection is disabled.
